[[File:酉の市Torinoichi000.jpg|thumb|{{ill|Tori-no-Ichi|ja|酉の市|1=Tori-no-Ichi|qq=draft|qq=draft}}の{{ill|Kumade|ja|熊手|qq=draft|qq=draft}}]] '''Ōtori Shrine''' (大鷲神社, also pronounced Ōwashi Shrine) refers to a name for various {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} across Japan. These shrines are part of the {{ill|Ōtori faith|ja|大鳥信仰|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, with {{ill|Ōtori Taisha|ja|大鳥大社|1=Ōtori taisha|qq=draft|qq=draft}} as their main shrine. Many are related to other shrines with similar names, such as {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|大鳥神社 (曖昧さ回避)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Washi Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|鷲神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Washi-no-Miya Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|鷲宮神社 (曖昧さ回避)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Several are also widely known for hosting {{ill|Tori-no-Ichi|ja|酉の市|1=Tori-no-Ichi|qq=draft|qq=draft}} festivals. There are seven such shrines officially recognized as religious corporations nationwide.
For related terms, see {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|大鳥神社 (曖昧さ回避)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Washi Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|鷲神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Washi-no-Miya Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|鷲宮神社 (曖昧さ回避)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Ame-no-Hiwashi Shrine (disambiguation)|ja|日鷲神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (Tsukuba)|ja|大鷲神社 (つくば市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in Tedegaki, Tsukuba City, Ibaraki Prefecture. * {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (Ichikawa)|ja|大鷲神社 (市川市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in Takaya, Ichikawa City, Chiba Prefecture. * {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (Ichihara)|ja|大鷲神社 (市原市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in Yanagihara, Ichihara City, Chiba Prefecture. * {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (Narita)|ja|大鷲神社 (成田市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in Kitahatori, Narita City, Chiba Prefecture. * {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (Sakae)|ja|大鷲神社 (栄町)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in Anjō, Sakae Town, Inba District, Chiba Prefecture. * {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (Shisui)|ja|大鷲神社 (酒々井町)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in Kamiiwahashi, Shisui Town, Inba District, Chiba Prefecture. * {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (Adachi)|ja|大鷲神社 (足立区)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in Hanahata, Adachi Ward, Tokyo. Known as the origin of Tori-no-Ichi. * Ōtori Shrine - Located in Miyamachi, Fuchū City, Tokyo. A subsidiary shrine of {{ill|Ōkunitama Shrine|ja|大國魂神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * Ōtori Shrine - Located in Makane-chō, Minami Ward, Yokohama City, Kanagawa Prefecture. Consolidated into the precincts of a {{ill|Konpira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (see {{ill|Konpira and Ōtori Shrine|ja|金刀比羅・大鷲神社|1=Konpira and Ōtori Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft}}).
